175
00:09:42,561 --> 00:09:43,993
He's warm.

176
00:09:43,993 --> 00:09:45,893
Yes, I guess so.

177
00:09:45,893 --> 00:09:48,567
So, the next time the men open the door,

178
00:09:48,567 --> 00:09:50,569
let's have them let us out!

179
00:09:50,569 --> 00:09:51,393
Yeah...

180
00:09:51,393 --> 00:09:54,193
No, I don't think we should.

181
00:09:54,193 --> 00:09:56,093
Huh...

182
00:09:56,093 --> 00:09:58,093
It seems somebody else...

183
00:09:58,093 --> 00:10:00,579
was already on this truck before us.

184
00:10:08,193 --> 00:10:10,093
Just what do you mean?

185
00:10:10,093 --> 00:10:11,693
I wonder...

186
00:10:11,693 --> 00:10:13,693
I don't know who or where he came from,

187
00:10:13,693 --> 00:10:16,893
nor do I know why he was killed,

188
00:10:16,893 --> 00:10:21,793
but I'm sure that the ones who did it are the two delivery men.

189
00:10:21,793 --> 00:10:23,193
What...

190
00:10:23,193 --> 00:10:24,993
Are you serious?

191
00:10:24,993 --> 00:10:28,607
But why is he in the back of the truck like this?

192
00:10:28,607 --> 00:10:31,893
Because this truck is equipped with a refrigeration device.

193
00:10:31,893 --> 00:10:33,593
Leaving him in here

194
00:10:33,593 --> 00:10:35,493
would delay the decaying process of the corpse,

195
00:10:35,493 --> 00:10:38,293
thus, also delay the estimated time of death.

