We've gotta watch out.

278
00:14:16,837 --> 00:14:19,837
The only delivery we have for the fourth district

279
00:14:19,837 --> 00:14:22,537
are the Yamada and Nishino residence?

280
00:14:22,537 --> 00:14:23,837
Yeah.

281
00:14:26,237 --> 00:14:27,837
But, before that,

282
00:14:27,837 --> 00:14:30,337
it's about time we move the box with the corpse inside.

283
00:14:30,337 --> 00:14:32,137
I guess so.

284
00:14:32,137 --> 00:14:34,437
It's already been about two hours.

285
00:14:36,037 --> 00:14:39,437
Here goes...

286
00:14:39,437 --> 00:14:42,437
Okay, now it'll keep for another two hours

287
00:14:42,437 --> 00:14:45,237
without livor mortis appearing.

288
00:14:45,237 --> 00:14:46,865
What's wrong?

289
00:14:46,865 --> 00:14:50,637
It looks like the masking tape had been pulled off once.

290
00:14:50,637 --> 00:14:51,737
Huh?

291
00:14:51,737 --> 00:14:54,537
You idiot! Just who are you saying pulled it off.

292
00:14:55,737 --> 00:14:57,637
-Oh, no. -What...

293
00:14:57,637 --> 00:14:59,937
I thought I just heard a cat...

294
00:14:59,937 --> 00:15:03,437
Heck, what's with you anyway?

295
00:15:03,437 --> 00:15:06,137
First, you say you hear the voices of kids,

296
00:15:06,137 --> 00:15:07,637
then now you say you hear a cat?

297
00:15:07,637 --> 00:15:09,337
But...

298
00:15:09,337 --> 00:15:11,737
Well, you did kill a person,

299
00:15:11,737 --> 00:15:14,237
so I can understand you feeling uncomfortable.

300
00:15:14,237 --> 00:15:16,037
I'm really sorry

301
00:15:16,037 --> 00:15:18,897
that things had to turn out this way just because of me.

302
00:15:18,897 --> 00:15:20,437
It can't be helped.

303
00:15:20,437 --> 00:15:22,437
It coincidentally turned out that the house you made a delivery to

304
00:15:22,437 --> 00:15:24,903
was the of the husband of the woman you were having an affair with,

305
00:15:25,137 --> 00:15:28,037
and he snapped and attacked you

306
00:15:28,037 --> 00:15:30,637
saying that you were to blame for him getting a divorce.

307
00:15:30,637 --> 00:15:32,937
I had no intention of killing him.

308
00:15:32,937 --> 00:15:35,837
I tried to pull free from his grasp and knocked him down.

309
00:15:35,837 --> 00:15:37,537
He hit his head somewhere

310
00:15:37,537 --> 00:15:39,737
and stopped moving completely.

311
00:15:39,737 --> 00:15:42,937
Well, you did then right thing

312
00:15:42,937 --> 00:15:44,923
to call me before contacting the police.

313
00:15:45,137 --> 00:15:47,237
We did get a hold of the wallet

314
00:15:47,237 --> 00:15:49,437
with a lot of cash in it too, besides.

315
00:15:49,437 --> 00:15:52,937
But, are you sure nobody's going to find out?

316
00:15:52,937 --> 00:15:54,637
Don't worry.

317
00:15:54,637 --> 00:15:55,837
After a while, we'll take the corpse back

318
00:15:55,837 --> 00:15:59,437
to his house where he previously was and leave him there.

319
00:15:59,437 --> 00:16:02,637
After some time, we'll go back to his place

320
00:16:02,637 --> 00:16:04,237
and contact the police telling them

321
00:16:04,237 --> 00:16:06,037
that we just found the body.

322
00:16:06,037 --> 00:16:07,937
Then, everything will be okay.

323
00:16:07,937 --> 00:16:10,337
I guess so.

324
00:16:10,337 --> 00:16:13,537
Well, we could crack a window glass

325
00:16:13,537 --> 00:16:16,337
to make them think that he was robbed and attacked.

326
00:16:18,037 --> 00:16:20,959
After all, we've got loads of people

327
00:16:20,959 --> 00:16:22,961
to prove our alibi.

328
00:16:22,961 --> 00:16:23,837
Yeah.

329
00:16:27,437 --> 00:16:28,967
I see.

330
00:16:28,967 --> 00:16:32,037
So, it turned out to be a homicide.

331
00:16:32,037 --> 00:16:34,437
At any rate, let's report this to Officer Takagi.

332
00:16:37,237 --> 00:16:40,537
We will be taking off soon.

333
00:16:40,537 --> 00:16:42,537
Please switch off your cell phones,

334
00:16:42,537 --> 00:16:48,037
laptops game and electronic devices etc.

335
00:16:48,037 --> 00:16:50,137
I am sorry.

336
00:16:50,137 --> 00:16:51,437
I was trying to confirm the vicinity

337
00:16:51,437 --> 00:16:52,991
of the Kyoto Prefectural Police area

338
00:16:52,991 --> 00:16:54,993
where we're supposed to go pick up the suspect,

339
00:16:54,993 --> 00:16:56,537
but how am I supposed to switch this off?

340
00:16:56,537 --> 00:16:59,837
Push the power switch down for a while!

341
00:17:02,137 --> 00:17:05,937
All because you bought a smartphone trying to look edgy.

342
00:17:05,937 --> 00:17:08,037
Did you switch yours off already?

343
00:17:08,037 --> 00:17:10,537
Yes! For some time already!

344
00:17:13,011 --> 00:17:14,737
The number you have called

345
00:17:14,737 --> 00:17:17,637
is out of service range or switched off.

346
00:17:17,637 --> 00:17:21,019
So, your call cannot be completed.

347
00:17:21,019 --> 00:17:22,737
No good, I can't get through.

348
00:17:22,737 --> 00:17:24,037
No.

349
00:17:24,037 --> 00:17:25,437
I've got no choice.

350
00:17:25,437 --> 00:17:28,337
I'll call Doc and explain our situation.

351
00:17:31,937 --> 00:17:34,837
Oh, yes, this is Agasa.

352
00:17:34,837 --> 00:17:36,837
Doc? It's me.

353
00:17:36,837 --> 00:17:38,637
Jot down what I'm about to tell you.

354
00:17:38,637 --> 00:17:40,137
Oh, I'm sorry.

355
00:17:40,137 --> 00:17:42,537
My hands are tied just yet.

356
00:17:42,537 --> 00:17:44,037
Hold on a minute.

357
00:17:44,037 --> 00:17:46,037
-Hey! -Hot!

358
00:17:46,037 --> 00:17:48,437
What's cooking?

359
00:17:48,437 --> 00:17:50,837
Okay.

360
00:17:50,837 --> 00:17:53,437
Hello, sorry to keep you waiting.

361
00:17:53,437 --> 00:17:55,437
I though just cake wouldn't be enough,

362
00:17:55,437 --> 00:17:57,637
so I was deep frying doughnuts.

363
00:17:57,637 --> 00:17:59,537
Well, it won't be as good

364
00:17:59,537 --> 00:18:02,837
as the exclusive Christmas cake from the famous shop, but...

365
00:18:04,137 --> 00:18:06,737
Huh? He hung up.

366
00:18:06,737 --> 00:18:08,137
Well, if it's anything important,

367
00:18:08,137 --> 00:18:10,737
I guess he'll call back.

368
00:18:10,737 --> 00:18:13,637
Darn, the battery's run out.

369
00:18:13,637 --> 00:18:15,937
Then, maybe if you warm it up again...

370
00:18:15,937 --> 00:18:17,937
Once the battery's completely used up,

371
00:18:17,937 --> 00:18:20,337
warming it up is not going to revive it.

372
00:18:20,337 --> 00:18:22,837
So, what now?

373
00:18:22,837 --> 00:18:26,737
You guys, put out what you have in front of me.

374
00:18:26,737 --> 00:18:29,087
I'll try thinking whether I can do something using them.

375
00:18:29,337 --> 00:18:32,137
Okay...

376
00:18:33,437 --> 00:18:38,837
I have a handkerchief, pocket tissue,

377
00:18:38,837 --> 00:18:41,099
candy and a cotton swab.

378
00:18:41,099 --> 00:18:42,337
The cotton swab is what was left

379
00:18:42,337 --> 00:18:45,637
after mommy cleaned my ears for me this morning.

380
00:18:45,637 --> 00:18:49,107
It's not used, so don't worry.

381
00:18:49,107 --> 00:18:51,109
-How about you, Genta? -I...

382
00:18:51,109 --> 00:18:54,537
I have a band-aid, chocolate bar,

383
00:18:54,537 --> 00:18:57,637
and anti-itching ointment for frost bites.

384
00:18:57,637 --> 00:18:58,837
Anti-itching ointment?

385
00:18:58,837 --> 00:19:02,237
Oh, I never got frost bites,

386
00:19:02,237 --> 00:19:05,537
but mom kept nagging me to keep it with me.

387
00:19:05,537 --> 00:19:06,637
And, what about you, Mitsuhiko?

388
00:19:06,637 --> 00:19:09,127
I...

389
00:19:09,127 --> 00:19:12,237
A memo pad, a bal point pen to go with it,

390
00:19:12,237 --> 00:19:16,337
handkerchief, a wallet, and a taxi receipt.

391
00:19:16,337 --> 00:19:18,237
A taxi receipt?

392
00:19:18,237 --> 00:19:21,437
Yes. When I woke up and was washing my face,

393
00:19:21,437 --> 00:19:24,337
I found it on the floor near the washing machine.

394
00:19:24,337 --> 00:19:27,437
Mother probably wanting to wash father's clothes,

395
00:19:27,437 --> 00:19:31,149
checked the pocket and it dropped out.

396
00:19:31,149 --> 00:19:34,437
I forgot to give it back to mother.

397
00:19:34,437 --> 00:19:38,437
Next the only thing I have left is the jacket I lent Haibara.

398
00:19:38,437 --> 00:19:41,637
I wore it right after it came back from the cleaners

399
00:19:41,637 --> 00:19:43,837
that I don't think there's anything inside.

400
00:19:43,837 --> 00:19:46,537
How about you, Haibara? Do you have anything?

401
00:19:46,537 --> 00:19:47,737
Huh?

402
00:19:47,737 --> 00:19:48,937
Oh, that's right.

403
00:19:48,937 --> 00:19:51,169
You only have underwear on you.

404
00:19:51,169 --> 00:19:52,137
Shut up.

405
00:19:56,737 --> 00:20:01,179
But, I don't think you can do with these things.

406
00:20:01,179 --> 00:20:03,737
How about writing help on a paper

407
00:20:03,737 --> 00:20:05,183
from Mitsuhiko's memo pad,

408
00:20:05,183 --> 00:20:09,187
tearing it off and dropping out of the car?

409
00:20:09,187 --> 00:20:11,537
Oh, that sounds good.

410
00:20:11,537 --> 00:20:12,937
With that much space under the door,

411
00:20:12,937 --> 00:20:15,193
it looks like we can push a paper through.

412
00:20:15,193 --> 00:20:19,197
But even if someone were to pick it up,

413
00:20:19,197 --> 00:20:22,537
there's no guarantee that they'll call the police right away.

414
00:20:22,537 --> 00:20:26,037
Besides, if we can get the paper outside, it'll be okay,

415
00:20:26,037 --> 00:20:27,205
but if it gets stuck and we can't get it outside,

416
00:20:27,205 --> 00:20:28,837
that's it for us.

417
00:20:28,837 --> 00:20:32,437
The next time the delivery men open the back door of the truck

418
00:20:32,437 --> 00:20:35,237
and find the paper stuck to the door,

419
00:20:35,237 --> 00:20:39,217
they'll find out that someone is inside.

420
00:20:39,217 --> 00:20:40,337
I see.

421
00:20:40,337 --> 00:20:42,037
Then, what're we going to do?

422
00:20:42,037 --> 00:20:44,737
-Beats me. -What do you mean, beats me?

423
00:20:47,637 --> 00:20:50,537
You sure are easygoing, aren't you?

424
00:20:50,537 --> 00:20:51,837
If only you didn't jump into

425
00:20:51,837 --> 00:20:55,233
the back of this truck to begin with...

426
00:20:59,237 --> 00:21:00,937
If I remember correctly, this cat...

427
00:21:02,837 --> 00:21:05,737
I get it! There's a way.

428
00:21:05,737 --> 00:21:09,737
No, but I guess that's too far-fetched.

429
00:21:09,737 --> 00:21:12,037
What? If you came up with something,

430
00:21:12,037 --> 00:21:13,251
tell us about it.

431
00:21:13,437 --> 00:21:16,037
Huh?

432
00:21:16,037 --> 00:21:19,257
The stop that this delivery truck made just before now

433
00:21:19,257 --> 00:21:21,259
was at Beika Condo in the third district.

434
00:21:21,259 --> 00:21:24,337
The two houses that they stopped at now was in the fourth district.

435
00:21:24,337 --> 00:21:25,937
So, the next stop would be?

436
00:21:25,937 --> 00:21:28,837
The fifth district?

437
00:21:28,837 --> 00:21:29,937
Right.

438
00:21:29,937 --> 00:21:32,337
The territory of this cat, Tai.

439
00:21:33,437 --> 00:21:36,137
The fifth district where he goes to beg for food

440
00:21:36,137 --> 00:21:38,437
at coffee shop Poirot.

441
00:21:38,437 --> 00:21:39,637
I see!

442
00:21:39,637 --> 00:21:40,837
You're going to make Tai go

443
00:21:40,837 --> 00:21:43,281
and deliver a note that asks help for us!

444
00:21:43,281 --> 00:21:44,937
If we stick it in between its collar,

445
00:21:44,937 --> 00:21:47,285
I'm sure Azusa will notice it!

446
00:21:47,537 --> 00:21:49,287
Let's do it!

447
00:21:49,287 --> 00:21:50,637
Yeah.

448
00:21:50,637 --> 00:21:52,337
But...

449
00:21:52,337 --> 00:21:54,637
If those two men catch Tai

450
00:21:54,637 --> 00:21:58,237
and see the paper attached to its collar...

451
00:21:58,237 --> 00:22:00,637
I've already figured that part out too.

452
00:22:00,637 --> 00:22:02,337
Huh?

453
00:22:02,337 --> 00:22:04,637
I'll think up a code that they won't figure out

454
00:22:04,637 --> 00:22:07,305
even if they were to see it.

455
00:22:07,305 --> 00:22:09,307
A code?

456
00:23:46,620 --> 00:23:48,180
Next Conan's Hint:

457
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:50,500
"Christmas Cake"

458
00:23:51,409 --> 00:23:53,000
I'd like chocolate.

459
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,220
Cake doesn't seem to go well with you.

460
00:23:54,220 --> 00:23:55,420
Do you want to be hit again?

